text: I think
America has always welcomed
entrepreneurs it's created good
environments for them it's create a good
Capital behind them a and I think it's
still a great place for great leaders
with vision and courage to launch an
idea I also believe that China and India
are welcoming entrepreneurs and
sponsoring entrepreneurs and there's
Capital flowing into those markets and
there's Capital flowing into parts of
Latin America and Australia and even
parts of Europe as well so I I don't
think America has a lock on the
entrepreneurial environment but I also
believe in America for a combination
of human needs whether it be you know a
need for control or a need for financial
success that some people have
tried to be entrepreneurs who aren't and
I think faux entrepreneurs actually
cause a problem because you see a lot of
people starting businesses but without
the courage and conviction to follow
them through I see less of that in some
of these other markets where it actually
is a bigger risk to become an
entrepreneur and therefore the
entrepreneurs are stronger and I think
what's going to be important in a more
Global world is that American
entrepreneurs understand that they don't
have a leg up that they have to compete
on a Level Playing Field and if they're
not as committed to their ideas as their
colleagues on the other side of the
world they're not going to win
